title: What would happen if Google disappears for a week? - Quora

response.answer_text: 1# CIA would go blind for a week 2# American democracy may improve as people reach to each other for answers  3# Businesses will shift from Adwords to Bing Ads, Yahoo! Bing Network Contextual Ads 4# Users will shift to alternative services Youtube > Dailymotion, VimeoGmail > Outlook.com, Yahoo MailG Search > Bing, DuckDuckGoGDrive > OneDriveAndroid> Windows Phone, iosG+ > Twitter, Pinterest, etc 5# All the authors who hate google scanning their books and making them available publicly will rejoice. 6# Piracy related to movies, music, games, software's will go down by more than 40% easily 7# Privacy of individual users will get a boost. No more tracking you around or scanning your emails to give you personalized ads. Which will allow you to concentrate on your emails or surfing. 8# The already extinct but not extinct PageRank (Greenbar) will achieve logical termination. And will be replaced by mozRank (see source 2# ) 9# Brick and mortar stores will see increase in sales over their e-commerce counterparts 10# All the android handsets will either get hacked or be installed with other supported Mobile Operating Systems 11# An Individual's IQ will improve (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Is_Google_Making_Us_Stupid%3F ) 12# 57000+ Employees of Google will need to buy their own lunch increasing traffic on sites like Zomato, FoodPanda etc., !! 13# The only website whose traffic will go down is google's itself  Sources:1# http://lifehacker.com/5876794/going-google-free-the-best-alternatives-to-google-services-on-the-web 2# http://mysiteauditor.com/blog/is-google-pagerank-dead/
